a noun is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAfu Alt~a$obiyhi","text_ar":"كَافُ التَّشْبِيهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k","text_ar":"ك"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of comparison."},{"kind":"text","text":"Respecting its being prefixed to pronouns, see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano","text_ar":"اَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", suprà, p. 106. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ijoEalo","text_ar":"اـِجْعَلْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA Al$~aYo'a kaA^osFA waAHidFA","text_ar":"هٰذَا الشَّىْءَ كَاْسًا وَاحِدًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Make thou this thing to be"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uniform,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of one way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, in TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bA^j","text_ar":"باج"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*`lika","text_ar":"كَذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The like thereof; such like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA_K","text_ar":"كَاـٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kA='K","text_ar":"كا=ءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA^aY~K","text_ar":"كَاَىٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA^ay~ino","text_ar":"كَاَيِّنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aY~N","text_ar":"اَىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamaA","text_ar":"كَمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"followed by a pret. often means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Like as when:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see an ex. in a verse cited above, p. 740. ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamaA","text_ar":"كَمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is often followed by a pret. in the sense of an aor.: see exs. in EM., pp. 41 & 214. ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamaA A^anota waziyodFA","text_ar":"كَمَا اَنْتَ وَزِيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keep as,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where, thou art, and approach not Zeyd!"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makaAnaka wazayodFA","text_ar":"مَكَانَكَ وَزَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. Heard by Ks. (L, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"End","text_ar":"عند"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamaAA^anotaniY","text_ar":"كَمَااَنْتَنِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wait for me where thou art!"},{"kind":"text","text":"Heard by Az from certain of the Benoo-Suleym. (L, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"End","text_ar":"عند"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k","text_ar":"ك"},{"kind":"text","text":"of allocution is varied like the pronominal affix of the sec. pers., accord. to the sex and number of the persons addressed: see exs. in the Kur, iii. 42 and xix. 21 (Flügel's ed., and Lees' Keshsháf), xii. 37, ii. 46, &c., and xii. 32. But sometimes the same form is used in addressing a number of persons as in addressing one man: see, for ex., Kur, iv. 96."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}